1
00:00:02,100 --> 00:00:03,651
"迷失"前情回顾...
Previously on "lost"...

2
00:00:03,664 --> 00:00:06,352
他们来了 开始争斗
They come. They fight.

3
00:00:06,352 --> 00:00:09,463
他们毁灭 最后腐烂
They destroy. They corrupt.

4
00:00:09,463 --> 00:00:10,692
结局总是相同的
It always ends the same.

5
00:00:11,992 --> 00:00:13,033
但是只结束一次
It only ends once.

6
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:17,125
在这之前所有的事情都是过程
Anything that happens before that is just progress.

7
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:19,253
我不会杀Jacob的 Ben
I'm not gonna kill Jacob, Ben.

8
00:00:20,453 --> 00:00:21,571
你会
You are.

9
00:00:21,871 --> 00:00:24,968
- 照我说的做 Ben - 我只想让你明白一件事情
- Do what I asked you to, Ben. - I want you to understand one thing.

10
00:00:26,468 --> 00:00:27,511
你有机会选择的
You have a choice.

11
00:00:30,836 --> 00:00:32,981
他们来了
They're coming.

12
00:00:38,281 --> 00:00:40,128
在天鹅站工地的达摩组织的人们...
The Dharma folks at the swan worksite...

13
00:00:40,128 --> 00:00:41,813
他们会在地上钻井
They're gonna drill into the ground

14
00:00:41,813 --> 00:00:44,539
意外的钻入了一块巨大的隐藏能量中
And accidentally tap into a massive pocket of energy.

15
00:00:44,539 --> 00:00:46,937
我觉得我能消除这股能量
I think I can negate that energy.

16
00:00:46,937 --> 00:00:51,963
- 我会去引爆氢弹的 - 如果我们按照Faraday说的做 飞机就不会失事
- I'm gonna detonate a hydrogen bomb. - If we can do what Faraday said, plane never crashes.

17
00:00:51,963 --> 00:00:54,575
815号航班会在洛杉矶降落
Flight 815 lands in los angeles.

18
00:00:56,542 --> 00:00:59,543
快点 医生! 你在等什么?!
Hurry up, Doc! What are you waitin' for?!

19
00:01:09,774 --> 00:01:11,201
我们钻到能量块了!
We hit the pocket!

20
00:01:18,273 --> 00:01:19,240
Juliet啊
Juliet!

21
00:01:21,774 --> 00:01:24,068
- 我抓住你了 不 不要松手! - 啊!
- I got you. No, don't let go! - Aah!

22
00:01:24,968 --> 00:01:25,986
Juliet啊
Juliet!

23
00:01:25,986 --> 00:01:27,342
不!
No!

24
00:01:36,351 --> 00:01:38,518
不! 不 快点!
No! No, come on!

25
00:01:38,518 --> 00:01:40,355
快点!
Come on!

26
00:01:40,355 --> 00:01:43,212
快点 你这混蛋!
Come on, you son of a bitch!

27
00:02:19,407 --> 00:02:21,013
饮料还满意么?
So how's the drink?

28
00:02:22,313 --> 00:02:24,172
呃...
Uh...

29
00:02:24,172 --> 00:02:25,692
还不错
It's good.

30
00:02:25,692 --> 00:02:27,894
这个反应可不够强烈啊
That's not a very strong reaction.

31
00:02:27,894 --> 00:02:31,291
好吧 这个... 也不是个烈性饮料
Well, it's... it's not a very strong drink.

32
00:02:34,096 --> 00:02:37,380
- 谁也别告诉 - 这是我们的秘密
- Don't tell anyone. - It'll be our secret.

33
00:02:47,282 --> 00:02:48,452
女士们先生们
Ladies and gentlemen,

34
00:02:48,452 --> 00:02:50,724
机长已将"系好安全带"指示打开
The captain has turned on the "fasten seat belts" sign.

35
00:02:50,774 --> 00:02:54,428
- 系好你们的安全带 - 这是正常情况
- And keep your seat belts fastened. - It's normal.

36
00:02:54,666 --> 00:02:57,763
我丈夫说了 这飞机想呆在天上
My husband said the planes want to stay in the air.

37
00:02:59,763 --> 00:03:01,225
听起来像个聪明人
Sounds like a smart man.

38
00:03:01,825 --> 00:03:02,737
绝对是的
You be sure and tell him that

39
00:03:02,737 --> 00:03:05,563
你可以等他从厕所回来把这句话告诉他
when he gets back from the bathroom.

40
00:03:05,563 --> 00:03:07,857
好啊 他不在的时候 我会陪着你的
Well, I'll keep you company until he does.

41
00:03:07,857 --> 00:03:09,281
别担心
Don't worry.

42
00:03:29,639 --> 00:03:31,891
你可以放开了
You can let go now.

43
00:03:35,551 --> 00:03:38,054
没事了 你... 你可以放手了
It's okay. You...you can let go.

44
00:03:47,136 --> 00:03:50,858
- 看来我们成功了 - 是啊 我们当然成功了
- Looks like we made it. - Yeah. We sure did.

45
00:03:50,858 --> 00:03:53,673
很抱歉出现了突然的撞击 大伙
Sorry about the unexpected bumps, folks.

46
00:03:53,673 --> 00:03:54,935
我们刚刚遇到一块扰动气流
We just hit a pocket of rough air.

47
00:03:54,935 --> 00:03:57,051
之后的旅途会很平稳
It should be a smooth ride from here on out.

48
00:03:57,651 --> 00:04:01,620
下次提醒我要憋着 好么?
Remind me to hold it next time, will ya?

49
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,512
我在厕所差点死过去
I almost died in that bathroom.

50
00:04:06,866 --> 00:04:09,680
我终于知道衣服在被烘干的时候是什么感觉了
Now I know how the laundry feels when it's in the dryer.

51
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:13,691
我想你了
I missed you.

52
00:04:15,091 --> 00:04:17,895
我也想你了 美女
I missed you, too, beautiful.

53
00:05:04,259 --> 00:05:07,435
- 对不起 - 哦 对不起 伙计 这是你的座位?
- Excuse me. - Oh, I'm sorry, mate. Is this your seat?

54
00:05:07,435 --> 00:05:10,292
- 乘务员说是空的 - 不 不 我是坐在窗边的
- The stewardess said it was empty. - No. No, I'm at the window.

55
00:05:10,292 --> 00:05:11,918
哦 好的
Oh, right.

56
00:05:17,559 --> 00:05:18,997
那么 伙计 你介意我坐这儿么?
Listen, mate, do you mind if I sit here?

57
00:05:19,008 --> 00:05:20,790
就是我边上的那个小伙子一直在打鼾
It's just the fella next to me has been snoring

58
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:24,360
- 我们从悉尼起飞之后就开始了 - 好的 没问题
Ever since we took off from sydney. Yeah, no problem.

59
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,784
谢了 兄弟
Thanks, brother.

60
00:05:38,687 --> 00:05:39,211
怎么了?
Something wrong?

61
00:05:39,211 --> 00:05:41,101
不 没事 只是你...
No. No, you just...

62
00:05:41,101 --> 00:05:43,114
我是不是认识你呢?
Do I know you from somewhere?

63
00:05:45,814 --> 00:05:47,946
啊 我也不确定
Well, I'm not sure.

64
00:05:50,092 --> 00:05:50,973
我叫Desmond
Desmond.

65
00:05:51,873 --> 00:05:52,777
嗯Jack
Jack.

66
00:05:52,777 --> 00:05:54,186
很高兴见到你 Jack...
Nice to meet you, Jack...

67
00:05:55,386 --> 00:05:57,341
或者说再次见到你
Or to see you again.

68
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:40,648
啊! 不! 不! Juliet!
Aah! No! No! Juliet!

69
00:07:42,382 --> 00:07:45,029
- 我抓住你了 不 别放手! - 啊!
- I got you. No, don't let go! - Aah!

70
00:07:45,529 --> 00:07:47,867
Juliet! 不!
Juliet! No!

71
00:07:50,660 --> 00:07:53,304
快点 你这混蛋!
Come on, you son of a bitch!

72
00:09:17,577 --> 00:09:19,093
喂?
Hello?

73
00:09:26,057 --> 00:09:27,448
喂?!
Hello?!

74
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:40,200
嘿!
Hey!

75
00:09:41,070 --> 00:09:43,082
嘿! 嘿! Kate!
Hey! Hey! Kate!

76
00:09:43,093 --> 00:09:45,835
好了好了 是我 Miles. 没事了
It's okay. It's me, Miles. It's okay.

77
00:09:48,753 --> 00:09:50,299
- 发生了什么? - 什么?
- What happened? - What?

78
00:09:50,299 --> 00:09:52,040
我们在哪?
Where are we?

79
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:54,678
我听不到... 你在说什么 你的耳朵有没有嗡嗡响?
I can't... I can't here you. Are your ears ringing?

80
00:09:58,922 --> 00:10:01,539
这是什么?
What is it?

81
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:06,530
我们又回来了
We're back.

82
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:07,781
回哪去了?
Back where?

83
00:10:19,856 --> 00:10:22,671
不
No.

84
00:10:22,671 --> 00:10:25,215
这不是工地么?
Is that the construction site?

85
00:10:25,215 --> 00:10:26,341
不
No.

86
00:10:26,342 --> 00:10:29,021
那是天鹅舱...
That's the swan hatch...

87
00:10:29,021 --> 00:10:31,107
Desmond炸过之后的
After Desmond blew it up.

88
00:10:31,107 --> 00:10:34,902
我猜我们没在1977年 哈?
Guess we're not in 1977, huh?

89
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:48,854
是Jack? Jack
Jack? Jack.

90
00:10:50,908 --> 00:10:54,318
你能听见我说话么? Jack!
Can you hear me? Jack!

91
00:10:56,226 --> 00:10:57,696
发生了什么?
What happened?

92
00:10:59,008 --> 00:11:03,327
- 我们在那? - 在舱门边上
- Where are we? - At the hatch.

93
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,707
什么? 他们还是造了这个?
What? They built it?

94
00:11:16,717 --> 00:11:21,154
对 他们造了
Yeah. They built it.

95
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:25,058
住手Sawyer!
Sawyer!

96
00:11:26,487 --> 00:11:27,665
呃!
Uhh!

97
00:11:27,665 --> 00:11:29,928
你错了!
You were wrong!

98
00:11:29,928 --> 00:11:32,621
那是该死的天鹅站舱口...
That's the damn swan hatch...

99
00:11:32,632 --> 00:11:35,474
爆炸过后就像是我们留下来的一样
Blown up just like we left it

100
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:38,712
在我们开始穿越时空之前!
Before we started jumping through time!

101
00:11:38,712 --> 00:11:41,231
你说过我们甚至可以阻止它建立!
You said we could stop it from ever gettin' built!

102
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,648
- 我们的飞机也不会坠落到这个岛! - 别这样了!
- That our plane would never crash on this island! - Stop it!

103
00:11:43,648 --> 00:11:45,901
- 这儿不是洛杉矶! - 别这样了!
- This ain't l.a.x.! - Stop it!

104
00:11:45,911 --> 00:11:48,341
你让我们白折腾了!
You blew us right back where we started!

105
00:11:48,341 --> 00:11:51,052
而Juliet却死了
Except Juliet's dead.

106
00:11:53,731 --> 00:11:58,538
她死了 你个狗娘养的 都是你的错
She's dead, you son of a bitch, 'cause you were wrong.

107
00:11:58,538 --> 00:12:02,188
Sawyer啊...
Sawyer...

108
00:12:02,188 --> 00:12:04,242
对不起
I'm sorry.

109
00:12:04,242 --> 00:12:07,683
我还以为我们会...
I thought we were supposed to...

110
00:12:07,683 --> 00:12:09,768
本以为会起作用的
I thought it would work.

111
00:12:09,779 --> 00:12:12,865
可它没有!
Well, it didn't!

112
00:12:24,717 --> 00:12:25,858
你在排队?
You in line?

113
00:12:25,859 --> 00:12:28,289
不 在等我的朋友
No, I'm just waiting for my friend.

114
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:31,451
- 哦! - 喔
- Oh! - Whoa.

115
00:12:31,451 --> 00:12:33,145
- 对不起 我没有... - 没关系
- I'm sorry. I didn't... - It's okay.

116
00:12:33,145 --> 00:12:34,962
- 我没看到你在这儿 - 没关系
- I didn't see you there. - It's okay.

117
00:12:34,973 --> 00:12:37,111
我们坐回去吧 亲爱的
Let's get back to our seats, sweetheart.

118
00:12:45,073 --> 00:12:46,832
嗯
Mmm.

119
00:12:47,032 --> 00:12:48,838
千层面
Lasagna.

120
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:54,851
别 别用刀叉 亲爱的
No. No knife and fork for you, honey.

121
00:12:54,851 --> 00:12:56,937
你觉得我会干嘛
What do you think I'm gonna do,&

122
00:12:56,937 --> 00:12:59,408
捅了你然后逃跑?
Stab you and run?

123
00:12:59,408 --> 00:13:02,296
嘿 走路看着点 伙计
Hey, watch we're you're going, buddy.

124
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:08,417
对不起 我的错
Sorry. My bad.

125
00:13:10,488 --> 00:13:12,572
说吧 好吗? 就一遍
Say it. Come on, please? Just once.

126
00:13:12,672 --> 00:13:15,623
- 我真不想这么干 兄弟 - 我爱死那广告了
- I really don't want to, dude. - I love those commercials.

127
00:13:15,634 --> 00:13:17,719
说吧 用澳洲口音说
Come on. Just do the Australian accent,

128
00:13:17,719 --> 00:13:19,804
我就不来烦你了
And I'll leave you alone.

129
00:13:19,804 --> 00:13:22,693
好吧 好吧 好吧
All right. Fine. All right.

130
00:13:22,693 --> 00:13:25,372
哦!开始咕咕咯咯的一天吧 伙计!
Oi! Have a cluckity-cluck day, mate!

131
00:13:30,659 --> 00:13:32,713
你知道这是谁吗?
You know who this is?

132
00:13:32,713 --> 00:13:34,737
这是... 是咯咯叫先生鸡肉店的老板
This is...this is the owner of Mr. Cluck's chicken.

133
00:13:34,737 --> 00:13:36,822
而他... 他现在正和我们一起
And he's...and he's back here riding coach

134
00:13:36,822 --> 00:13:40,378
- 坐在飞机上! 对吧? - 那又怎么了?
- With the rest of us yutzes! Huh? - How about th?

135
00:13:40,378 --> 00:13:42,735
嘿 嗯 我能问下
Hey, um, do you mind me asking,

136
00:13:42,745 --> 00:13:45,800
像你这样的人是如何有了这么大的一家公司的呢?
How exactly did a guy like you get to own a major corporation?

137
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,928
我中了彩票又喜欢吃鸡
I won the lottery and I like chicken,

138
00:13:48,928 --> 00:13:51,024
就把它买下喽
So I bought it.

139
00:13:51,024 --> 00:13:53,381
噢 真好
Oh. Good.

140
00:13:53,391 --> 00:13:55,330
你真行
Good for you.

141
00:13:57,843 --> 00:14:01,253
你知道吗 你真不该告诉其他人你中奖了
You know, you really shouldn't tell people you won the lottery.

142
00:14:01,253 --> 00:14:03,338
是吗? 为什么?
Yeah? Why not?

143
00:14:03,338 --> 00:14:06,779
因为他们会利用你 这就是原因
Cause they'll take advantage of you. That's why not.

144
00:14:06,779 --> 00:14:10,085
谢谢你的忠告 兄弟 但这不会发生的
Thanks for the advice, dude, but it's not gonna happen.

145
00:14:10,085 --> 00:14:12,660
不会 是吗?
It's not, huh?

146
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:16,039
是的 我运气向来很好
Nope. Nothing bad ever happens to me.

147
00:14:16,039 --> 00:14:18,572
我是世界上最幸运的人
I'm the luckiest guy alive.

148
00:14:30,423 --> 00:14:31,585
刚刚怎么了?
What just happened?

149
00:14:31,585 --> 00:14:33,254
我看到了一阵闪光
I found a flashlight.

150
00:14:33,254 --> 00:14:36,632
兄弟 谁在乎啊? 白昼瞬间成黑夜了
Dude, who cares? The sky just went from day to night.

151
00:14:36,632 --> 00:14:39,176
- 怎么回事啊?! - 我猜我们是穿越时空了
- What happened?! - I think we moved through time.

152
00:14:39,476 --> 00:14:41,053
你怎么知道?
How do you know that?

153
00:14:41,053 --> 00:14:44,383
白色闪光 头痛 听不见声音
White flash. Headache. Can't hear.

154
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:47,101
- 我以前也发生过 - Jack和其他人呢?
- Happened to me before. - What about Jack and everyone else?

155
00:14:47,101 --> 00:14:48,835
- 他们也穿越时空了吗? - 我不知道
- Did they move through time, too? - I don't know.

156
00:14:48,835 --> 00:14:51,600
他们开了另外一辆货车去工地了
They took one of the other vans and went up to the worksite.

157
00:14:51,611 --> 00:14:53,696
接着我就听到了枪声...
And then I heard gunfire...

158
00:14:53,696 --> 00:14:55,497
- 嘘! - 你说过我们的飞机再也不会坠到这个岛上的!
- Shh! - You said that our plane would never crash on this island!

159
00:14:55,497 --> 00:15:00,382
- 听到了吗 兄弟? 是Sawyer - 呆这儿陪着Sayid
- You hear that, dude? It's Sawyer. - Stay here with Sayid.

160
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,285
炸弹肯定爆炸了
The bomb must've gone off.

161
00:15:06,285 --> 00:15:09,205
你觉得原子弹爆炸了以后我们还能站在这儿?
You think an atom bomb went off, we'd still be standing here?!

162
00:15:09,205 --> 00:15:10,263
我不懂
I don't know.

163
00:15:10,263 --> 00:15:13,866
没错! 你不懂! 你终于承认不懂了!
That's right! You don't! For once, you don't know!

164
00:15:13,866 --> 00:15:16,337
Jack啊!
Jack!

165
00:15:16,337 --> 00:15:18,047
Sayid需要帮助
Sayid needs help.

166
00:15:18,047 --> 00:15:20,012
- 他在哪儿? - 在货车那儿 Hurley陪着他
- Where is he? - With Hurley at the van.

167
00:15:20,023 --> 00:15:21,139
- 两分钟路程 - 救命
- Two minutes away. - Help.

168
00:15:21,139 --> 00:15:23,309
他还在流血 我们不知道该怎么办
He's still bleeding. We don't know what to do.

169
00:15:25,909 --> 00:15:29,006
救命
Help me.

170
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,211
怎么说啊 医生?
So what do you say, doc?

171
00:15:31,211 --> 00:15:33,382
又想到一个好主意来救Sayid了?
Got another great idea to save Sayid?

172
00:15:33,382 --> 00:15:35,806
- 没准周围又埋了一颗核弹 - 嘿 闭嘴!
- Maybe there's a nuke laying around. - Hey, shut up!

173
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,622
救命
Help.

174
00:15:47,856 --> 00:15:49,535
Juliet啊
Juliet!

175
00:15:49,935 --> 00:15:50,864
James吗?
James?

176
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:52,860
噢 天呐
Oh, my god.

177
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:54,318
Juliet啊!
Juliet!

178
00:15:58,989 --> 00:16:00,929
哦 天呐 哦 天呐 恶心死了
Oh, god. Oh, god, this is gross.

179
00:16:06,121 --> 00:16:07,748
别担心 兄弟
Don't worry, dude.

180
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:09,562
一切都会好起来的
Everything's gonna be fine.

181
00:16:12,608 --> 00:16:14,088
我死后...
When I die...

182
00:16:16,695 --> 00:16:20,240
你觉得我会发生什么?
What do you think will happen to me?

183
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,336
别... 别说话了 哥们
Just... just try not to talk, dude.

184
00:16:22,336 --> 00:16:25,495
我虐待过多少人自己都记不清了
I've tortured more people than I can remember.

185
00:16:27,059 --> 00:16:28,936
我杀人
I murdered.

186
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:32,700
不管我去哪儿...
Wherever I'm going...

187
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,486
都不会是好地方
It can't be very pleasant.

188
00:16:34,486 --> 00:16:37,465
- Sayid 行了 - 我活该
- Sayid, come on. - I deserve it.

189
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:45,505
谁?
Hello?

190
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:50,927
Jin吗?
Jin?

191
00:16:55,348 --> 00:16:56,391
Jin啊
Jin!

192
00:17:00,009 --> 00:17:02,457
我有枪的!
I've got a gun!

193
00:17:02,457 --> 00:17:05,191
我也知道怎么用!
And I know how to shoot it!

194
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,868
你好 Hugo
Hello, Hugo.

195
00:17:35,278 --> 00:17:37,989
有时间吗?
You got a minute?

196
00:17:50,338 --> 00:17:52,598

你盯着他们干吗?

197
00:17:53,536 --> 00:17:56,560

他们看起来挺开心的

198
00:18:00,561 --> 00:18:02,712

把衣服扣上

199
00:18:14,148 --> 00:18:16,484
你在浪费时间 伙计
You're wasting your time, man.

200
00:18:18,061 --> 00:18:19,585
这架飞机要是在大海中间坠落的话
This plane goes down in the ocean way out here,

201
00:18:19,585 --> 00:18:24,242
我想我们的生存几率绝对为零
I think our chances of survival are exactly zero.

202
00:18:24,242 --> 00:18:28,517
实际上 平静的海面再加一个好的飞行员
Actually, in calm seas w-with a good pilot,

203
00:18:28,517 --> 00:18:30,584
我们可以在水面迫降的
We could survive a water landing.

204
00:18:30,584 --> 00:18:33,147
还有 嗯 燃料罐浮力很大的
And, uh, the fuel tanks are buoyant enough

205
00:18:33,147 --> 00:18:35,618
完全可以支持到我们上救生筏
To keep us afloat until we got in the life rafts.

206
00:18:36,869 --> 00:18:38,089
怎么了?
What?

207
00:18:38,089 --> 00:18:40,175
没什么 你知道的可真不少
No, it's just impressive you know that.

208
00:18:41,634 --> 00:18:43,647
你在澳大利亚干吗了?
What were you doing in Australia?

209
00:18:43,657 --> 00:18:46,118
生意还是度假?
Business or pleasure?

210
00:18:46,118 --> 00:18:48,454
度假 你呢?
Pleasure. You?

211
00:18:48,454 --> 00:18:52,697
我去处理一下和我妹妹糟糕的关系
I went down to get my sister out of a bad relationship

212
00:18:52,697 --> 00:18:56,837
结果是她不买我的帐
That it turns out she didn't want to get out of.

213
00:18:56,837 --> 00:18:58,401
如此...
So...

214
00:18:58,401 --> 00:19:00,424
我就在这儿了
Here I am.

215
00:19:00,424 --> 00:19:03,761
那么说 你是来澳洲度假的了?
So what, you were just down under for vacation?

216
00:19:04,161 --> 00:19:06,576
实际上 我是来徒步旅行的
Actually, I went on a walkabout.

217
00:19:06,576 --> 00:19:08,964
是吗?
Really?

218
00:19:08,964 --> 00:19:11,977
就像... 像鳄鱼邓迪似的?
Like... like Crocodile Cundee?&

219
00:19:11,977 --> 00:19:13,885
不 不太像
No, not exactly.

220
00:19:13,885 --> 00:19:16,012
但... 但是 嗯 相当激烈了
But... but, uh, it was pretty intense.

221
00:19:16,012 --> 00:19:18,932
我们... 我们在内陆呆了10天
We... we spent ten days in the outback

222
00:19:18,932 --> 00:19:21,674
嗯 除了包和刀什么都不带
And, uh, nothing but our packs and our knives.

223
00:19:21,685 --> 00:19:24,236
我们燃起篝火 在星空下入睡
We slept under the stars and made our own fires,

224
00:19:24,236 --> 00:19:26,150
自己打猎
Hunted our own food.

225
00:19:26,150 --> 00:19:28,045
哇
Wow.

226
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:32,737
我要是两天不带电话就活不了
I wouldn't make it two days without my cell phone.

227
00:19:34,270 --> 00:19:36,741
你不是在跟我开玩笑吧 对吗?
You're not pulling my leg, are ya?

228
00:19:36,741 --> 00:19:39,556
我为什么要跟你开玩笑呢?
Why would I pull your leg?

229
00:19:41,537 --> 00:19:45,291
我的事完了之后 就跟你混一阵
This thing goes down, I'm sticking with you.

230
00:20:17,004 --> 00:20:21,160
你不用盯着火看了
You can stop staring at the fire.

231
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:26,415
Jacob死了
Jacob's gone.

232
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,683
他死了
He's gone.

233
00:20:28,693 --> 00:20:31,227
他为什么不还手?
Why didn't he fight back?

234
00:20:33,250 --> 00:20:35,752
他为什么让我杀他?
Why did he let me just kill him?

235
00:20:35,752 --> 00:20:38,286
我想是他知道他已经被打败了
I guess he knew that he was beaten.

236
00:20:42,116 --> 00:20:43,896
Ben啊...
Ben...

237
00:20:43,896 --> 00:20:45,440
我要你出去
I want you to go outside

238
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:50,048
告诉Richard 我想跟他谈谈
And tell Richard that I need to talk to him.

239
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:53,072
跟他谈... 什么?
Talk to him about... What?

240
00:20:54,082 --> 00:20:56,315
那是我和Richard的事
That's between me and Richard.

241
00:21:01,007 --> 00:21:04,145
- 没有别的原因 - 不 事情不应该那样的
- There's no other reason. - No, that's not how it's gonna be.

242
00:21:04,145 --> 00:21:06,856
- 你应该... - 你不能进去
- You have to... - you're not going in there.

243
00:21:06,856 --> 00:21:10,370
听我说 我已经决定了 现在我要你...
Listen to me. I already did. Now I'm asking you to...

244
00:21:10,370 --> 00:21:12,633
到那边去...
Body over by the...

245
00:21:13,957 --> 00:21:16,043
只要退回去一点 好吗?
Just back up a little. Okay?

246
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,733
他们是谁?
Who are they?

247
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:21,818
除了那些
Other than the fact

248
00:21:21,818 --> 00:21:24,634
和我们一起在Ajira航班上的人
that I know they were on the Ajira flight with us,

249
00:21:24,634 --> 00:21:26,761
我所知道的就是 他们打晕了我
All I know is they knocked me out

250
00:21:26,761 --> 00:21:28,638
把我关进了某个小屋
And dragged my ass to some cabin,

251
00:21:28,638 --> 00:21:30,995
他们很快又把屋子给烧了 然后
Which they promptly burned, then...

252
00:21:30,995 --> 00:21:35,248
把我和棺材里那个死人又带到了这里
Brought me here along with the dead guy in the box.

253
00:21:35,248 --> 00:21:38,064
他们说他们是好人
They say they're the good guys.

254
00:21:41,477 --> 00:21:43,379
我也不信
I'm not buying it either.

255
00:21:45,863 --> 00:21:48,856
听我说 嘿! 听我说 给我仔细听着
Listen to me. Hey! Listen to me, and listen carefully.

256
00:21:48,856 --> 00:21:50,534
除非Jacob邀请 否则谁也不能进去
No one goes in there unless Jacob invites them in.

257
00:21:50,544 --> 00:21:54,739
Richard 我们之所以来这里 就是因为Jacob邀请了我们
Richard, that's why we're here, because Jacob invited us.

258
00:21:54,749 --> 00:21:56,327
问我那该死的雕像下边有什么
Asking me what's in the shadow of the damn statue

259
00:21:56,338 --> 00:21:58,598
- 并不代表你是头儿 - 那谁是呢?
- Doesn't mean you're in charge. - Then who is?

260
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,759
Richard啊
Richard.

261
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:04,068
嘿 Ben
Ben.

262
00:22:04,068 --> 00:22:06,477
里面怎么了?
What happened in there?

263
00:22:06,477 --> 00:22:08,249
一切都好
Everything's fine.

264
00:22:08,249 --> 00:22:10,721
John想跟你谈谈
John wants to speak to you.

265
00:22:10,721 --> 00:22:13,309
- Jacob还好吧? - 不好意思 你哪位?
- Is Jacob all right? - I'm sorry. Who are you?

266
00:22:13,309 --> 00:22:16,437
- 回答她的问题 Ben - 哦 那当然 Jacob很好
- Answer her question, Ben. - Well, of course Jacob's all right.

267
00:22:16,437 --> 00:22:20,545
他们两个都在里面 John想跟你谈谈
They're both together inside. John just wants to talk to you.

268
00:22:20,545 --> 00:22:23,496
- John想跟我谈谈? - 是的
- John wants to talk to me? - That's right.

269
00:22:23,496 --> 00:22:26,635
Richard 你干什么? 我不明白
Richard, what are you doing? I don't understand.

270
00:22:26,635 --> 00:22:28,142
哦 跟John谈话我很高兴
Well, I'm happy to talk to John.

271
00:22:28,442 --> 00:22:32,338
但在我跟他谈之前 你最好先跟他谈谈
But before I do, maybe you should talk to him first.

272
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:56,591
坚持住 Juliet! 我们马上到!
Hang on, Juliet! We're coming!

273
00:22:59,867 --> 00:23:01,253
呃!
Uhh!

274
00:23:05,095 --> 00:23:08,107
Jin 手电筒
Jin. Flashlight.

275
00:23:11,188 --> 00:23:15,378
把这根柱子移开 我就能下去了
We can move this beam. Think I can get down there.

276
00:23:28,884 --> 00:23:33,193
唉! 这太重了 得拿点东西把这个拉起来 Jin!
Uhh! Too heavy. We need something to pull it. Jin!

277
00:23:33,193 --> 00:23:36,566
货车! 里面有条链子 拿过来!
The van! There's chains in it. Go get 'em!

278
00:23:45,057 --> 00:23:46,767
老兄 你在干啥?
Where you going, dude?

279
00:23:46,867 --> 00:23:49,284
你跑这儿干啥?
And what are you doing here?

280
00:23:49,284 --> 00:23:51,707
我在计程车里见过你
I mean, I meet you in a taxi,

281
00:23:51,707 --> 00:23:53,343
你知道我的一切
and you know everything about me,

282
00:23:53,343 --> 00:23:54,695
你还给了我一张
and you give me a plane ticket,

283
00:23:54,695 --> 00:23:56,805
刚好能把我送回岛上的机票
which just so happens to get me back on this island.

284
00:23:56,805 --> 00:24:00,234
你怎么知道将要发生的事?
How'd you know that was gonna happen?

285
00:24:01,319 --> 00:24:03,028
听得到吗?
Hello?

286
00:24:06,325 --> 00:24:10,593
能听得到吗? 为什么不回答我的问题?
Can you hear me? Why aren't you answering my questions?

287
00:24:10,630 --> 00:24:12,501
我朋友Jin随时都可能回来
Look, my friend Jin's gonna be here any second,

288
00:24:12,501 --> 00:24:15,537
- 你最好不要再忽略我了... - 你朋友Jin见不到我了
- So you better stop ignoring me... - Your friend Jin won't be able to see me.

289
00:24:15,537 --> 00:24:17,180
为啥?
Why not?

290
00:24:17,280 --> 00:24:21,241
因为我一小时前就死了
Because I died an hour ago.

291
00:24:21,241 --> 00:24:24,024
抱歉 老兄 不好受吧
Sorry, dude. That sucks.

292
00:24:24,024 --> 00:24:25,417
谢谢
Thanks.

293
00:24:25,417 --> 00:24:27,461
怎么死的?
How'd you die?

294
00:24:27,461 --> 00:24:31,791
被一个已经厌倦了我陪伴的老朋友杀的
I was killed by an old friend who grew tired of my company.

295
00:24:36,411 --> 00:24:39,107
你又想让我做什么疯狂的事了 是吧?
You want me to do something crazy again, don't you?

296
00:24:39,107 --> 00:24:42,186
不 Hugo 我要你救活Sayid
No. I need you to save Sayid, Hugo.

297
00:24:42,186 --> 00:24:45,736
- 所以Jin去找Jack 让他... - Jin帮不了的
- Well, that's why Jin went to go get Jack, to... - Jin can't help him.

298
00:24:45,736 --> 00:24:48,763
你要把Sayid带到庙里
You need to take Sayid to the temple.

299
00:24:48,763 --> 00:24:50,584
这是他活命的唯一机会
That's the only chance he's got.

300
00:24:50,584 --> 00:24:52,545
其他的人在那也会安全的
And the rest of them will be safe there.

301
00:24:52,645 --> 00:24:54,851
庙? 我应该知道那是什么吧?
The temple? I'm supposed to know what that is?

302
00:24:54,851 --> 00:24:56,503
Jin知道
Jin knows.

303
00:24:56,503 --> 00:24:58,266
让他带你去有洞的那堵墙
Tell him to take you to the hole in the wall

304
00:24:58,266 --> 00:25:00,153
他和法国人曾去过那里
where he was with the French team.

305
00:25:00,153 --> 00:25:03,027
经过那个入口 你们就能到庙里去了
Through that opening, you can get into the temple.

306
00:25:03,327 --> 00:25:05,983
你还拿着我给你的吉他盒吧?
You still have that guitar case I gave you?

307
00:25:06,932 --> 00:25:07,745
对
Yeah.

308
00:25:07,845 --> 00:25:10,835
带上它
Bring it.

309
00:25:11,329 --> 00:25:13,878
老兄 你是谁?
Who are you, dude?

310
00:25:14,078 --> 00:25:16,533
我是Jacob
I'm Jacob.

311
00:25:22,340 --> 00:25:23,515
Hurley啊!
Hurley!

312
00:25:25,015 --> 00:25:26,276
帮我抬一下Sayid
Help me with Sayid.

313
00:25:26,276 --> 00:25:30,007
我们得把他放到车里面 Juliet需要帮忙
We have to get him into the van. Juliet needs our help.

314
00:25:30,007 --> 00:25:32,793
快! 该走了!
Come on! We have to go!

315
00:25:42,237 --> 00:25:43,710
Jin 如果我让你
Jin, if I asked you

316
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:46,029
带我去那个带洞的墙那里
to take me to where there's like a hole in the wall,

317
00:25:46,029 --> 00:25:47,747
就是你当初和法国人去过的地方
where you went with the french team,

318
00:25:47,747 --> 00:25:49,939
你知道我在说什么吗?
would you know what I was talking about?

319
00:25:51,339 --> 00:25:52,418
知道
Yes.

320
00:25:52,418 --> 00:25:54,386
很好
Good.

321
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,512
我去拿链子
I'll get the chain.

322
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,522
Juliet呢?
Juliet?

323
00:26:11,122 --> 00:26:12,157
冷静 Sawyer 冷静
Stop it. Stop, Sawyer.

324
00:26:12,157 --> 00:26:15,600
车已经到了 链子马上就来了
The van is here. The chains are comin'.

325
00:26:23,917 --> 00:26:27,987
- 她已经不出声了 - 她知道我们在这儿 她应该在休息
- She ain't makin' any more noises. - She knows we're here. She's probably just resting.

326
00:26:27,987 --> 00:26:30,073
Juliet啊!
Juliet!

327
00:26:36,959 --> 00:26:39,467
如果她死了 我一定会杀了他
If she dies, I'll kill him.

328
00:26:45,913 --> 00:26:48,288
女士们先生们 没有任何紧急情况
Ladies and gentlemen, nothing to be alarmed about,

329
00:26:48,288 --> 00:26:49,372
如果您是医生
but if there is a doctor on board,

330
00:26:49,372 --> 00:26:52,245
请按下您的呼叫按钮
would you please press your call button?

331
00:26:55,242 --> 00:26:57,005
- 先生 您是医生? - 是
- Sir, you're a doctor? - Yes.

332
00:26:57,005 --> 00:27:00,801
您能不能跟我来呢? 非常感谢您的帮助
Could you come with me, please? We appreciate your help.

333
00:27:00,801 --> 00:27:03,289
一位乘客半小时前 进了洗手间
A passenger went into the restroom about half an hour ago,

334
00:27:03,289 --> 00:27:05,155
但我们敲门却没人答应
and he's not responding when we knock.

335
00:27:05,955 --> 00:27:09,121
- 这位先生是医生 如果他昏迷了的话... - 我... 我觉得他把锁弄坏了
- This man's a doctor. If he's unconscious in there... - I... I think he tampered with the lock.

336
00:27:09,121 --> 00:27:10,653
锁... 锁好像被堵住了 我也不清楚
It's... it's jammed or something. I don't know.

337
00:27:10,753 --> 00:27:15,499
我能帮忙吗? 让一下
Can I be of assistance? Excuse me.

338
00:27:27,699 --> 00:27:29,977
他没有呼吸了
He's not breathing.

339
00:27:38,229 --> 00:27:39,920
后面怎么了 Earhart?
What's goin' on back there, Earhart?

340
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:44,151
- 一切平安 先生 请做好 - 好吧 看上去也正常着呢
- Yeah, everything's fine, sir. Please just stay in your seat. - Yeah. Looks peachy.

341
00:27:44,351 --> 00:27:47,310
- 先生 我需要你帮忙 - 我能做什么?
- Sir, I'm gonna need your help. - What can I do?

342
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:49,744
我需要你...
I need you...

343
00:27:49,744 --> 00:27:51,046
把这个按在他的口鼻上
Hold this over his nose and mouth.

344
00:27:51,046 --> 00:27:54,677
- 按住 不要让空气跑出来了 - 好的 现在吗?
- Hold it there, and do not let any air escape. - Okay. Now?

345
00:27:54,677 --> 00:27:56,472
是的 现在
Yes, now.

346
00:28:00,983 --> 00:28:03,973
有什么东西卡在气管上了
Something's blocking his air passage.

347
00:28:09,285 --> 00:28:10,376
必须打通
We have to open it up.

348
00:28:10,376 --> 00:28:13,575
我需要 呃 尖锐的东西... 刮胡刀那样的
I need, uh, something sharp... a razor.

349
00:28:14,899 --> 00:28:16,603
- 我有支笔 - 笔?
- I got a pen. - A pen?

350
00:28:16,603 --> 00:28:20,327
- 有规定 飞机上不能带尖锐的东西 - 笔! 一支笔就够了
- It's regulation. There's nothing sharp. - A pen! Just a pen.

351
00:28:20,327 --> 00:28:23,597
本来我的外套有支笔的 但是不见了
I had a pen in my jacket but it's gone.

352
00:28:23,597 --> 00:28:25,648
该死
Damn it.

353
00:28:30,864 --> 00:28:32,959
拿到了 拿到了
I got it. I got it.

354
00:28:41,563 --> 00:28:46,244
放松 放轻松 呼吸
Relax. Just relax. Breathe.

355
00:28:50,117 --> 00:28:51,744
我还活着?
I'm alive?

356
00:28:51,744 --> 00:28:55,599
对 你还活着
Yeah. Ah, you're alive.

357
00:28:57,502 --> 00:29:00,230
真可怕
